Returns a point by evaluating the position along a circle.
The position is specified by a t parameter that starts at 0 and ends at 1.
If the circle object is closed, 0 and 1 will have the same position.
Values for of t<0 and t>1 are valid, they will loop around.
If the circle object is an open arc, the 0 will be the start of the arc, and 1 will be the end of the arc.
Values for of t<0 and t>1 are automatically converted to 0 and 1 respectively.

If the circle object is closed, 0 and 1 will have the same position.

The point is projected onto the closest point on the circle, and t is then caclulated for that point.

Creates a new list by making a copy of an existing list.

New duplicated list.

copy = List.Copy(list)

New list.

Adds an item to the end of a list.

comment.returns:
New list with added item.

Example:

list = [1,2,3]
append = List.append(list,4)

Expected value of list is [1,2,3,4].

comment.shortText:

comment.returns:
New list with added item.

Example:

list = [1,2,3]
append = List.appendFront(list,4)

Expected value of list is [4,1,2,3].

comment.shortText:
Adds items (from a list) to the end of an list.
Items are added to list individually as seperate items.

List with added items.

Example:

list = [1,2,3]
list2 = [9,0]
extend = List.extend(list,list2)

Expected value of extend is [1,2,3,9,0].

comment.shortText:

List with added items.

list = [1,2,3]
list2 = [9,0]
extend = List.extend(list,list2)

Expected value of extend is [9,0,1,2,3].

Expected value of len is 3.

List with item removed.

List with item removed

remove = List.removeValue(list,2,true)

comment.text:
Removes all instances of specified value if true, removes only the first instance if
     false.

New reversed list.

Example:

list = [1,2,3]
result = List.reverse(list)

Expected value of result is [3,2,1].

comment.shortText: Creates a copy of a portion of a list, from start index to end index (end not included).
comment.returns:
A new list.

Example:

list = [1,2,3,4,5]
result = List.slice(list,1,3)

Expected value of result is [2,3].

comment.text:
Zero-based index at which to begin slicing.
     A negative index can be used, indicating an offset from the end of the sequence.
     If start is undefined, slice begins from index 0.

Zero-based index before which to end slicing. Slice extracts up to but not including end.
     A negative index can be used, indicating an offset from the end of the sequence.
     If end is undefined, slice extracts through the end of the sequence.

comment.shortText: Sorts a list of strings alphabetically. If items are not strings, they are treated as strings.
comment.text:
Items are sorted according to string Unicode code points (character by character, numbers before upper case
alphabets, upper case alphabets before lower case alphabets)
comment.returns:
New sorted list.

Example:

list = ["1","2","10","Orange","apple"]
sort = List.sortAlpha(list)

Expected value of list is ["1","10","2","Orange","apple"].

comment.shortText:

The list must contain numbers.
comment.returns:
New sorted list.

Example:

list = [56,6,48]

Expected value of list is [6,48,56].

comment.shortText: Adds and/or removes items to/from a list.

comment.returns:
A new list.

Example:

Checks if a string ends with a specified end string.
comment.returns:
True if str ends with search_str, false otherwise.

Example:

string = "Orange"
result = String.endsWith(string,"ge")
Expected value of result is true.

comment.shortText: Checks if a string contains a specified search string.
comment.returns:
True if str contains search_str, false otherwise.

Example:

string = "Orange"
incl = String.includes(string,"an")
Expected value of incl is true.

comment.shortText: Returns the number of characters in a string.
comment.returns:
Length of string.

Example:

string = "Orange"
length = String.len(string)
Expected value of length is 6.

comment.shortText:
Searches for and replaces the specified search string in a string.
The search string can also be a regular expression.
comment.returns:
New string with replaced characters.

Example:

string = "Orange"
newString = String.Replace(string,"O","Ar")
Expected value of newString is "Arrange".

comment.text: Sub-string or regular expression to search for.

comment.shortText:
Returns the position index of the first occurance of the specified search string within a string.
If the specified sub-string cannot be found, then returns -1.
comment.returns:
Number that represents position of search_str in str.

Example:

string = "Orange"
search = String.search(string,"e")
Expected value of search is 5.

comment.text: Sub-string or regular expression to search for.

comment.shortText: Splits a string into a list of substrings using a specified separator string.
comment.returns:
List of substrings.

Example:

string = "Orange"
split = String.split(string,"a")
Expected value of split is ["Or","nge"].

comment.text: String of characters used to split string.

comment.shortText: Checks if a string starts with the specified start string.
comment.returns:
True if str starts with search_str, false otherwise.

Example:

string = "Orange"
result = String.startsWith(string,"Or")
Expected value of result is true.

comment.shortText:
Extracts characters in a string between two specified indices and returns it as a new string.
Start index is inclusive and end index is exclusive.
comment.returns:
New string with extracted characters.

Example:

string = "Orange"
substring = String.substring(string,1,4)
Expected value of ends is "ran".

comment.text: Zero-based index to start extracting characters (inclusive).
Zero-based index to stop extracting characters (exclusive).
